data.title: Ones, Selena

data.text:
Released in 2002, Ones is a compilation of tragic Latin singer Selena's major-label recordings. Ignoring her self-titled EMI debut, it features tracks from the three 1990-1994 studio albums recorded before her untimely death, Ven Conmigo, Entre a Mi Mundo, and in particular, Amor Prohibido, from which eight songs are included. Alongside U.S. Latin number ones "Buenos Amigos," "Donde Quiera Que Estes," and "No Me Queda Mas," there are two tracks from her 1990 live LP, two songs from her posthumous albums, and an original medley of three of her biggest hits.

&copy Jon O'Brien /TiVo
